story.title: Unknown Caller - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: This Halloween, someone from Kelly’s past wants revenge – someone who knows her deepest, darkest secret.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Tamara Mataya is a New York Times and USA Today bestselling author,  a ghostwriter, a librarian, and a musician with synesthesia. She puts the S in TWSS and the B in LGBTQIA+.

story.prePaywallNotification: Was Kelly romantically involved with the strange person who is texting her? Keep reading UNKNOWN CALLER.
story.postPaywallNotification: Can Kelly figure out who her UNKNOWN CALLER is before it’s too late? Read the rest of the story.

messages.text: What are you doing for Halloween, Kelly?
Making you remember who I am.
What do you mean? Tell me who you are.
There’s no way you’ve forgotten me.
I don’t think so. It’s more fun this way.
And you liked to dress up…
Not so fast. There are rules to every game.
Both of us get to ask questions.
But you already know who I am, so…?
Sure, but it’s been a while.
Both of us get to ask questions.
And we have to tell the truth.
For this to work, we can’t lie to each other.
But how will I know YOU’RE telling the truth?
I don’t even know who this is.
Or HAS lied in their life.
Tonight there will be consequences for lying.
For me to make you scream?
It’s a perfect night for it.
And it wouldn’t be the first time you screamed for me.
You could be David playing a Halloween prank.
But I promise I can make you forget all about him.
And we HAVE to answer each other.
Would you like to ask the first question?
Ladies first? Sure. What’s your name?
Don’t suck the fun out of this by being prosaic.
Prosaic…that’s too fancy of a word for David.
I told you already, I’m not David.
Stop fishing for info and ask your question.
We went out a few times.
But we weren’t in a relationship?
That’s a second question. No cheating.
I thought we were just asking questions as they occurred to us.
We are, but I thought of a good one.
Average height. Athletic build. Black hair, blue eyes.
Mmm. I’m not mad at any of that!
Thank you. You never had any complaints before.
Come on, just tell me your name.
I used to, but not anymore.
Have you ever broken someone’s heart?
I don’t think so. I’m usually the dumped rather than the dumper.
Don’t talk to me about fair.
Did I do something to you?
You did this to yourself by asking the wrong thing.
Have you ever known someone who was murdered?
Who is this? I’m seriously asking now.
Stop! Tell me who this is.
You know what, I don’t think I want to play this game anymore.
Let me be more specific. Have you ever seen a dead body?
You’re sick. Who the hell is this?!
I know all your secrets, Kelly.
Everyone lies, or has lied in their life.
And if you don’t play with me…
Kelly drops her phone and it vibrates with another text. Her fingers tremble as she picks it up.
Who is that? In the pic?
Do NOT play stupid right now.
We both know exactly who that is.
Pants on fire. A truth about me? I ALWAYS call bluffs, Kelly.
It’s not your turn to ask a question.
I suggest you figure it out.
